# People Segmentation Dataset

## Data sources
The original data come from [supervisely](https://supervise.ly/),
you could also refer to the [blog](https://hackernoon.com/releasing-supervisely-person-dataset-for-teaching-machines-to-segment-humans-1f1fc1f28469).
 Thanks for their wonderful work.

## Specification
The dataset contains 5110 for training and 568 images for validation.
The files in `segmentation` directory contains the image list.
You could use it to train your segmentation model.

## Directory Structure
people_segmentation
├── images
│   └── *.jpg  # images for segmentation
│── masks
│   └── *.png  # segmentation masks corresponds to the images
└── segmentation
    │── train.txt  # image list for training
    │── trainval.txt  # all images
    └── val.txt  # image list for validation
